<summary>Its been a while (Super Paper Mario) (2/4/26)</summary>
<p>It has been  a while since I've actually posted here, but for the zero people who read this blog welcome back :)</p>
<p>I've been gone a while simply because I procastinate a lot and spend a l ot of time not doing thing sproductivily, anyways, now I'm back, I'll try to post more things :)</p>
<p >Super Paper Mario:

Super Paper Mario is one of the most loved and interesting games from Nintendo; it focuses on different dimensions, primarily flipping between the 3rd and 2nd dimensions. The game’s unique mechanics make the game so much more interesting and intriguing than (in my opinion) The Thousand-Year Door. 
<img src="https://mefloyd.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/screen-shot-2020-04-20-at-4.01.36-am.png?w=1200">
In this part, I will discuss the general plot of Super Paper Mario, level by level.
<br>

<em><h3>Plot!!!</h3></em> 

The game starts off with Princess Peach being kidnapped, and Mario and Luigi (obviously) need to save her. However, after breaking into Bowser’s Castle, they realise that Bowser did NOT kidnap Peach, and it was actually the result of another villain, known as Count Bleck. Count Bleck then kidnapped Peach and sucked everyone but Mario into some sort of black hole.
Mario then wakes up and meets with the game’s main partner, Tippi. And after travelling to Flipside, we meet Merlin, who tells us about the 7 pure hearts, which could stop the world from ending. (This is simplified a lot).
<br><br>
<strong>World 1</strong>
<br><br>
After Mario accepts the mission and returns the first pure heart. Mario travels to the first world, 1-1. In 1-1, the game introduces its new turn-based combat system, and everything is being done on one screen. Mario then grants the ability to flip into the third dimension. 
<br><br>
<img src="https://mario.wiki.gallery/images/thumb/0/0e/SPM_Lineland_Road.png/1200px-SPM_Lineland_Road.png">

In 1-2, Yold Town, we meet one of the many Pixls. The Pixls are (sort of) like partners in the game, and we first meet one named Throu. Thoreau has the ability to throw things by grabbing them with the 1 button. After this, you cross a few free bridges, and the level ends.
<br><br>
In 1-3, Mario meets Oh Chunks. O chunks in fact is one of Super Paper Mario's Main characters, or villians to be clear, he is used a lot in the game, but he is fun with his... scottish accent???
<br><br>
In 1-4, Mario meets Fragtail.  Where we are forced to fight him, the boss fight revolves around you having to jump on his back and attack him with enemies on his back. There's actually a cool trick where you can jump on his back again and deal infinite damage.
</p>
<img src="https://i.ytimg.com/vi/2x8JEdy9-9E/maxresdefault.jpg">
<p> Thanks for reading the first part of THE Super Paper Mario reviews! (if i remember to post)</p>
<em>-scrit</em>
