    <summary>Animal Crossing City Folk (12/3/25)</summary>
    <p>Animal Crossing City Folk is a fun game released in 2009 for the Nintendo Wii. The game is famous for being very similar to <a>Animal Crossing Wild World</a>, but I think it's not; it displays so many fun and interesting qualities that it's hard to ignore.</p>
    <em><strong>A run-down of the game</strong></em>
    <br><br>
    <img src="https://dodo.ac/np/images/thumb/0/0e/CF_Rover_Bus.png/300px-CF_Rover_Bus.png">
    <p>The game starts you off with Rover, who asks a lot of questions about you, such as your name, age, birthday, etc. This is a clever way to ask the player about things without making a boring menu screen, and I think it adds so much more charm to the game.</p>
    <p>We meet <a href="https://nookipedia.com/wiki/Tom_Nook">Tom Nook</a>, who does a lot of things, like giving you your house (and your debt, grrr...), explaining the store, and helping you meet and socialize with villagers. This serves as the "tutorial" of the game and helps new players understand its core, even if they've never touched a video game before.</p>
    <p>After this, the game lets you do <em>whatever</em> you want. Planting flowers, talking to villagers, upgrading Tom Nook's store, or visiting the city.</p>
    <em><strong>The city</strong></em>
    <img src="https://dodo.ac/np/images/thumb/3/38/CF_City.jpg/600px-CF_City.jpg">
    <p>The game is called City Folk, so you would think that the city plays a huge role in the game. The truth is, it does not; at least it doesn't force you to play it.</p>
    <p>The game has a whole city section, featuring <em>GracieGrace</em> for hair and beauty, <em>Crazy Redd's</em> for paintings, and many <a href="https://nookipedia.com/wiki/City">more</a>. The thing that makes the city section interesting is that it does not force or require you to go to the city; it is simply there for you. In fact, when I first played this game, I had no idea that this even existed! :)</p>
    <em><strong>Conclusion and Judgment</strong></em>
    <p>Animal Crossing City Folk is an amazing game, featuring amazing villagers, locations, and people. The game truly is something I will always have in my heart, and compared to <a href="http://mariowiki.com/New_Super_Mario_Bros._Wii">New Super Mario Bros</a>, I do have more attachment to this game and proper memories associated with it (sorry, New Super Mario Bros Wii :/)</p>
    <p>I highly recommend you play it and try it out, as I think it compares to <a href="https://nookipedia.com/wiki/Animal_Crossing:_New_Horizons">Animal Crossing New Horizons</a> as a game.</p>
    <em><strong>Yes, sorry for my upload schedule</strong></em>
    <p>I've been lazy lately, and the excuse from last post was simply because I was tired and had no motivation (sorry lol).</p>
    <p>All jokes aside, I am working on something—not toooo big, but hopefully a good startup or something like that. I hope this long post will make up for the two days without posting.</p>
    <em>-scrit</em>
